程序包 org.cloudbus.cloudsim.provisioners

类 PeProvisioner

java.lang.Object
org.cloudbus.cloudsim.provisioners.PeProvisioner
直接已知子类:
PeProvisionerSimple
public abstract class PeProvisioner
extends java.lang.Object
/** PeProvisioner is an abstract class that represents the provisioning policy used by a host to allocate its PEs to virtual machines inside it. It gets a physical PE and manage it in order to provide this PE as virtual PEs for VMs. In that way, a given PE might be shared among different VMs. Each host's PE has to have its own instance of a PeProvisioner. When extending this class, care must be taken to guarantee that the field availableMips will always contain the amount of free mips available for future allocations.
从以下版本开始:
CloudSim Toolkit 2.0

      public abstract boolean allocateMipsForVm​(Vm vm, double mips)
      Allocates a new virtual PE with a specific capacity for a given VM. The virtual PE to be added will use the total or partial mips capacity of the physical PE.
      参数:
      vm - the virtual machine for which the new virtual PE is being allocated
      mips - the mips to be allocated to the virtual PE of the given VM
      返回:
      $true if the virtual PE could be allocated; $false otherwise
